      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Taking a lower dose without proper monitoring is a direct invitation for a serious medical event. Feeling \"normal\" is not a substitute for laboratory confirmation of your blood clotting time. If you are concerned about the hassle, try a quick telehealth consultation with your provider to discuss a temporary adjustment plan. Never self-adjust anticoagulants based on a feeling; that is how serious complications start.",
      "source": "target",
